result.adr_address: 12 Smithfield, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.name: McDonald's

reviews.text: Really liked the special menu sea salt chocolate ice cream, very tasty. Are they just testing this here, at this specific McDonald’s or in Hong Kong? Roll this out, it is not in the outlet near my hotel in HK Cybercity or in Japan right now.  Nice taste, good dark chocolate waffle cone.
Sometimes overcrowded but good quality is above average compare to other branches. The toilet is quite dirty though.
Never heard of them before, but menu seems to be based around burgers. Good service, although fries could be hotter.
I mean it's McDonald's. It's decently cleaned, sometimes they forget my damn order. It's McDonald's what do you expect?

Today I visited McDonald's branch in Chi Fu Landmark. I ordered my favorite Mushroom Angus Beef Burger. This is a set meal including hamburger, a corn cup and a milk tea. Altogether it costs only HK$40, fair price. Besides, I found that the afternoon tea meal is very economical. You only need to pay HK$16 to get a hamburger and drink.

result.formatted_address: 香港堅尼地城士美菲路12號
result.name: 麥當勞

reviews.text: 要上樓上😥
地處四環中心區域，24小時營業，香港大學宿舍就在附近，方便了辛辛學子裏腹之便。
近地鐵出口、附近有巴士站、小巴站；方便
華富邨麥當勞，食物跟其他店一起睇齊，但員工服務實在太差，出餐時間長，比其他店舖多出两至三倍時間，我不只一次幫襯，每次需時最少二十分鐘，哎…
啲雞翼係即刻炸㗎, 畀餐的姨姨好友善, 今次上層 座位嘅位置又ok,夠乾淨喎。
